    'faq.rib.diff': 'What is the difference between UPF 50+ and regular fabric?',
    'faq.rib.diff.a': 'UPF 50+ fabric blocks 98% of UV radiation, allowing only 1/50th of UV rays to penetrate. Regular cotton or untreated fabric typically offers UPF 5-15. Seekingtex UPF 50+ fabrics maintain their protection rating even after repeated washing.',
    'faq.rib.engine': 'How does waterproof breathable fabric work?',
    'faq.rib.engine.a': 'Waterproof breathable fabrics use a microporous membrane (ePTFE, PU, or TPU) or a durable water-repellent (DWR) coating. The micropores are small enough to block liquid water droplets but large enough to let water vapor (sweat) escape, keeping you dry inside and out.',
    'faq.rib.beginner': 'What makes a fabric quick-dry?',
    'faq.rib.beginner.a': 'Quick-dry fabrics use hydrophobic synthetic fibers (polyester, nylon) or hydrophilic finishes that actively wick moisture away from the skin and spread it across a larger surface area for rapid evaporation. They dry 3-5x faster than cotton.',
    'faq.rib.maintenance': 'How do I care for UPF sun protection fabric?',
    'faq.rib.maintenance.a': 'Machine wash cold with mild detergent. Avoid bleach and fabric softener which degrade UV protection. Tumble dry low or line dry. Proper care maintains UPF rating for the garment lifetime.',
    'faq.inflatable.lifespan': 'How long does waterproof fabric last?',
    'faq.inflatable.lifespan.a': 'With proper care, waterproof breathable fabrics maintain performance for 3-5 years of regular use. Key factors: proper washing with tech wash, avoiding fabric softeners, and periodically reapplying DWR coating.',
    'faq.inflatable.storage': 'How should I store waterproof garments?',
    'faq.inflatable.storage.a': 'Store clean and completely dry in a cool, dark place. Avoid prolonged compression which can damage the membrane. Use breathable garment bags. Never store damp as this can cause delamination.',
    'faq.inflatable.maintenance': 'What maintenance does performance fabric need?',
    'faq.inflatable.maintenance.a': 'Wash with tech wash after exposure to salt, chlorine, or heavy sweat. Air dry. Re-activate DWR with heat when water stops beading. Store clean and dry.',
