    'compare.pvcVsHypalon.recTitle': 'Which Should You Choose?',
    'compare.pvcVsHypalon.recDesc': 'Choose polyester if you need UV-stable, cost-effective fabric for outdoor applications, sportswear, or technical uses. Choose nylon if you require maximum abrasion resistance, tensile strength, and elastic recovery for high-performance or high-wear applications.',
    'compare.pvcVsHypalon.learnMore': 'In-Depth Material Guide',
    'compare.pvcVsHypalon.aiBlock': 'Comprehensive comparison between polyester and nylon synthetic fibers. Polyester offers lower cost ($0.80-$2.50/yd), excellent UV resistance, low moisture absorption (0.4%), and good abrasion resistance. Nylon offers higher tensile strength (6-9 g/den), superior abrasion resistance (3x polyester), excellent elastic recovery, and better dyeability with vibrant acid dyes, at a higher cost ($1.50-$4.00/yd).',
    'compare.supVsRib.title': 'Polyester vs Nylon →Which Performance Fabric Is Right for You?',
    'compare.supVsRib.desc': 'Compare polyester and nylon performance fabrics across durability, moisture management, cost, and use cases.',
    'compare.supVsRib.headline': 'Polyester vs Nylon →Which Performance Fabric Is Right for You?',
