    'compare.supVsRib.recTitle': 'Which Should You Choose?',
    'compare.supVsRib.recDesc': 'Choose polyester if you need UV-stable, cost-effective fabric for outdoor applications, sportswear, or technical uses where quick drying and moisture wicking are critical. Choose nylon if you require maximum abrasion resistance, tensile strength, and elastic recovery for high-performance or high-wear applications. Many textile products combine both through blending or layering to leverage the strengths of each fiber.',
    'compare.supVsRib.aiBlock': 'Comprehensive comparison between polyester and nylon synthetic fibers for textile applications. Covers tensile strength, abrasion resistance, UV stability, moisture absorption, drying speed, elastic recovery, cost, dyeability, melting point, chemical resistance, pilling resistance, and recyclability. Polyester offers excellent UV stability, low moisture absorption (0.4%), $0.80-$2.50 per yard, and is widely recycled. Nylon offers 3x the abrasion resistance, higher tensile strength (6-9 g/den), excellent elastic recovery, $1.50-$4.00 per yard, and takes vibrant acid dyes.',
    'nav.resources': 'Resources',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.title': 'Natural vs Synthetic Fiber →Which Is Better for You?',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.desc': 'Compare natural and synthetic fibers across performance, durability, sustainability, cost, and use cases. Make an informed fabric selection decision.',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.headline': 'Natural vs Synthetic Fiber →Which Is Better for You?',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.short': 'Natural vs Synthetic',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.heading': 'Natural vs Synthetic Fiber',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.subtitle': 'A comprehensive comparison between natural and synthetic fibers →covering everything a textile buyer needs to know.',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.col1Title': 'Natural Fibers',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.col2Title': 'Synthetic Fibers',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.portability': 'Breathability:',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.portDesc': 'Excellent natural breathability. Fibers absorb and release moisture, regulating body temperature effectively.',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.durability': 'Durability:',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.durDesc': 'Variable by fiber. Cotton is moderate, wool is excellent, silk is delicate. Susceptible to UV degradation, mildew, and pests.',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.performance': 'Comfort:',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.perfDesc': 'Superior comfort against skin. Natural softness, hypoallergenic properties. Wool offers natural temperature regulation.',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.storage': 'Sustainability:',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.storDesc': 'Biodegradable and renewable. Lower carbon footprint in production. Organic options avoid pesticides. Higher water and land use.',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.bestFor': 'Best for:',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.bestDesc': 'Everyday apparel, luxury garments, bedding, towels, environmentally conscious consumers, sensitive skin applications.',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.hardPortDesc': 'Less breathable naturally. Engineered finishes (wicking, ventilation) improve moisture management. Performance fabrics rival natural breathability.',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.hardDurDesc': 'Excellent durability. Resistant to abrasion, UV, mildew, chemicals. Polyester and nylon significantly outlast natural fibers in demanding conditions.',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.hardPerfDesc': 'Engineered for specific functions: moisture wicking, water resistance, flame retardancy, stretch, antimicrobial. Consistent quality batch to batch.',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.hardStorDesc': 'Derived from petroleum. Non-biodegradable. However, recycled polyester (rPET) and nylon recycling programs reduce environmental impact. Lower water usage than natural fibers.',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.hardBestDesc': 'Sportswear, outdoor gear, technical textiles, uniforms, industrial applications, high-performance apparel, cost-sensitive projects.',
    'compare.inflatableVsHard.tableTitle': 'Side-by-Side Comparison',
