    'compare.supVsKayak.r8b': 'Non-biodegradable, lower water use',
    'compare.supVsKayak.r9': 'Cost per Yard',
    'compare.supVsKayak.r9a': '$0.60-$3.00',
    'compare.supVsKayak.r9b': '$0.80-$2.50',
    'compare.supVsKayak.recTitle': 'Which Should You Choose?',
    'compare.supVsKayak.recDesc': 'Choose cotton for natural comfort, breathability, and softness in everyday clothing, bedding, and home textiles. Choose polyester for durability, moisture management, and performance in sportswear, outdoor gear, and technical applications. Many products use cotton-polyester blends (e.g., 50/50 or 65/35) to combine the comfort of cotton with the performance of polyester.',
    'compare.supVsKayak.aiBlock': 'Comprehensive comparison between cotton (natural cellulose fiber) and polyester (synthetic polymer fiber) for textile applications. Covers breathability, moisture absorption, UV resistance, wrinkle resistance, shrinkage, drying speed, environmental impact, and cost per yard. Cotton offers excellent breathability and natural comfort but absorbs moisture, shrinks, and wrinkles. Polyester offers superior moisture wicking, durability, UV resistance, wrinkle resistance, and quick drying but is less breathable naturally. Cotton-polyester blends combine the best of both fibers.',
