    'faq.inflatable.lifespan.a': 'PVC inflatable boats last 8? years with proper care. Hypalon boats can last 15?+ years. Proper inflation, fresh water rinsing, and avoiding sharp objects extend lifespan significantly.',
    'faq.inflatable.maintenance.a': 'Basic maintenance: rinse with fresh water after each use, dry thoroughly before storage, check for leaks at seams and valves, lubricate valves yearly with silicone grease.',
    'faq.inflatable.repair.a': 'Yes. Small punctures and seam leaks can be repaired with a PVC repair kit. Larger damage may require professional repair. Hypalon requires two-part adhesive and more careful preparation.',
    'faq.inflatable.storage': 'Can I leave my inflatable boat inflated all season?',
    'faq.inflatable.storage.a': 'Yes, but with precautions. Inflate to the rated pressure and check weekly as temperature changes affect pressure. Use a cover if storing outdoors.',
    'faq.rib.beginner': 'Are RIBs suitable for beginners?',
    'faq.rib.beginner.a': 'Smaller RIBs (2.5?3 m) with 10? HP engines are suitable for beginners in calm waters. Larger RIBs require boating experience due to higher speeds and handling characteristics.',
    'faq.rib.diff.a': 'A RIB (Rigid Inflatable Boat) combines a solid fiberglass or aluminum hull with inflatable tubes, offering superior handling in rough water. An inflatable boat has a fully flexible hull made entirely of PVC or Hypalon tubes →lighter and more portable but less capable in challenging conditions.',
    'faq.rib.engine': 'What size engine do I need for a RIB?',
    'faq.rib.engine.a': 'Engine size depends on your RIB length and intended use. A 3.3 m RIB typically handles 15? HP for recreation. A 4.5 m patrol RIB needs 40? HP for planing speeds. Always check the manufacturer\\\'s max engine rating.',
    'faq.rib.maintenance.a': 'Hypalon tubes require minimal maintenance. Rinse with fresh water after saltwater use, avoid prolonged UV exposure when deflated, and clean with mild soap and water.',
    'faq.sup.box': 'What comes in the box?',
    'faq.sup.box.a': 'Every Seekingtex SUP includes the board, a travel backpack, dual-action hand pump, removable fin, coil leash, and repair kit. Some models also include a carbon paddle upgrade option.',
    'faq.sup.learn': 'Is SUP hard to learn?',
    'faq.sup.learn.a': 'Not at all. Most beginners stand up and paddle within their first session. Our All-Around SUP series features extra-wide stable platforms designed specifically for first-time paddlers.',
    'faq.sup.travel': 'Can I travel with an inflatable SUP?',
    'faq.sup.travel.a': 'Absolutely. Every Seekingtex board packs into a backpack-sized carrying case that meets airline luggage requirements. At just 18? lbs, it is easy to carry anywhere.',
    'faq.sup.weight': 'What is the weight limit?',
    'faq.sup.weight.a': 'Our All-Around SUPs support up to 220 lbs. The Touring and Yoga series support up to 250 lbs.',
